17/04/2007
STRASBOURG, France -- Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe (PACE) President Rene van der Linden said on Monday (April 16th) that he expects Montenegro would soon accede to the CoE, becoming its 47th member.
PACE's spring session opened on Monday in Strasbourg.
Its agenda includes a vote on a proposal to recommend that the CoE Committee of Ministers endorse Montenegro's entry.
(Vijesti - 17/04/07;
Mina, RTCG - 16/04/07)
